<section id="fs-id1495558" type="ap-test-prep" class="ap-test-prep"><title>Test Prep for AP Courses</title><exercise id="fs-id1541667" type="ap-test-prep">
<problem id="fs-id2539802">
<para id="fs-id1184926">Two particles with charges +2<emphasis effect="italics">q</emphasis> and +<emphasis effect="italics">q</emphasis> are separated by a distance <emphasis effect="italics">r</emphasis>. The +2<emphasis effect="italics">q</emphasis> particle has an electric field <emphasis effect="italics">E</emphasis> at distance <emphasis effect="italics">r</emphasis> and exerts a force <emphasis effect="italics">F</emphasis> on the +<emphasis effect="italics">q</emphasis> particle. Use this information to answer questions 31–32.</para>

<para id="fs-id1299506">What is the electric field of the +<emphasis effect="italics">q</emphasis> particle at the same distance and what force does it exert on the +2<emphasis effect="italics">q</emphasis> particle?</para>
